 particuarly note that there were no sharks or sailors in Erud's Crossing (zone was completely empty of people too).<br>
<br>
Oasis - piece of cake if you can get wolf form from a druid.  Ask nicely and be willing to donate. <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
<br>
Unrest - Easy also, just run along the right side wall.  You might need enduring breath if you aren't comfortable with the location underwater.  I &quot;almost&quot; ran out of breath.<br>
<br>
Dagnor's Cauldron - This one was a bit scary.  I used levitate to find the general location and viewed underwater for a while.  I couldn't see the rod from the top.  I finally (with SoW for faster swimming) just dove for it and managed to find it against the wall.  Didn't have much trouble with lack of breath and was invisible; had no problem with aqua goblins as none were near.<br>
<br>
Qeynos - this one was very easy.  I went in from the north wall entrance and used my map from eqatlas.com to get to the shark pit.  No aggro problems of any sort for me (Erudite Agnostic).<br>
<br>
Highpass - this one is simple also.  I just invis'd myself to avoid orcs and gnolls and jumped in the water to get the wand.<br>
<br>
Lake Rathe - This one was easy, but the leg-work was in finding a druid willing to assist me.  You NEED enduring breath for this one and wolf-form is very preferable.  I had fish scales and 10pp (yes i'm poor) ready and was able to get a druid to assist me.<br>
<br>
Everfrost - You will need enduring breath for this one also.  I tried to go without and when my breath was at half, I turned around.  Once I was in the tunnel, I saw a Lich and his pet (both very red to me).  However, I just waited and they moved down the tunnel, finally going the opposite direction of the house holding the wand.  I was very nervous about the 3 green skeles <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->   I didn't have invis to undead.  I buffed up with damage shield, major shielding, and cold resist buff.  Once at full health and mana, I stood as far from the house as I could and used Lightning bolt on the skeleton I could see through the door.  He didn't move, however another popped on me from somewhere (not sure where).  I proceeded to bolt the skele in the house to death and then rooted the other one that was on me.  I then killed the rooted skele.  With one left in the house, I ran in and got the wand.  I rooted the other skeleton and used my remaning mana to gate out.<br>
<br>
Neriak - I simply used invis after I had explored the zones with a newbie dark elf.  Luckily, my invis didn't drop as I was moving to get the rod.  I then just gated out from the bank opposite the Priest of Discord.<br>
<br>
Erud's Crossing - I saved this for next to last as I was very nervous about the sharks.  I got all preped and read the guides and everything.  Well, I showed up and didn't see any sharks or zombie sailors.  Someone else I talked to hadn't seen any sharks either.  So I just swam down and got the rod.  Not sure if the zone has been changed or what, but this was one of the easiest to get.<br>
<br>
Lower Guk - Tried to find assistance last night.  I will try again tonight <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
<br>
I just wanted to share the adventures of a young wizard seeking his Staff of Wheel.  With a little help from others, this quest is very doable at 24.  Levitate is extremely helpful with certain rods (Dagnor's, Erud's Crossing).  I was invisible for basically every rod attempt, just as habit and a safety precaution.<br>
<br>
Zralgon<br>
